column1: To report the gain in life expectancy at birth, temporally distinct adjacent periods are subtracted. The year 2001- 2006 reflects the gain between 2001 to 2003 and 2004 to 2006, and similarly years 2011-2016 between 2011 to 2013 and 2014 to 2016.
A negative sign indicates that life expectancy at birth has fallen between temporally distinct periods.
Local areas are lower tier local authorities (LTLAs) in England, Unitary Authorities in Wales, Council Areas in Scotland and Local Government Districts in Northern Ireland.
